-- Infinis Acquires a Portfolio of Three U.K. Onshore Wind Farms
-- B y   M a r c   R o c a
-- 2012-05-08T09:05:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/infinis-acquires-a-portfolio-of-three-u-k-onshore-wind-farms.html
Infinis Group, an investment company
owned by  Guy Hands ’s Terra Firma Capital Partners Ltd., said it
bought three wind farms in the U.K. with a capacity of about 25
megawatts.  Two of the facilities are operating, and another is under
construction, Infinis said in a statement today. It didn’t
disclose a purchase price.  To contact the reporter on this story:
